            "value": "Rohan Sharma-Jones is a product of blended worlds. Born in Oakland to an Indian father, a pragmatic software engineer, and a free-spirited white American mother who was a ceramicist, his childhood was a sensory tapestry of curry spices, kiln dust, and lively dinner parties. The East Bay\u2019s diverse culinary landscape was his playground, and by his teens, he was more interested in the composition of a five-course meal than in coding. This passion led him to pursue a Bachelor\u2019s in Hospitality Management, a practical choice that worried his father but felt like destiny to him.\n\nHis career began humbly: bussing tables, then bartending through college. The turning point came during a post-graduation backpacking trip through Spain's Rioja region. Standing in a centuries-old vineyard, the concept of *terroir*\u2014the taste of a place\u2014crystallized in his mind. He returned to San Francisco with a new mission: to tell stories through beverages. He worked his way up with relentless dedication, earning a sommelier certification and making a name for himself with his innovative pairings. Now, as the Beverage Director for a chic, arts-focused restaurant in Hayes Valley, he curates a list that is both a conversation starter and a journey in a glass.\n\nRohan lives in a meticulously kept Duboce Triangle apartment with his husband, David, an architect. His 3.5-mile commute is a daily ritual he cherishes. Zipping through traffic on his Vespa is his moment of urban meditation, a burst of freedom before the orchestrated chaos of service begins. His days are a mix of meetings with distributors, training staff, and long nights on the restaurant floor, observing guests and ensuring every detail of the beverage experience is perfect.\n\nHis connection to San Francisco is profound; he sees the city as a living ecosystem of taste, constantly evolving. He thrives on the competition and camaraderie of its food scene. Rohan\u2019s ultimate dream is to open his own intimate bar in a neighborhood like the Mission or North Beach\u2014a small, personal space dedicated to artisanal spirits and natural wines. It would be the culmination of his life\u2019s work: a place that, like himself, is a thoughtful blend of heritage, craft, and modern San Francisco style."
