            "@type": "PropertyValue",
            "name": "reveries",
            "value": "1.\nHe was ten, weaving through a loud Oakland dinner party. His mother\u2019s earthy, clay-dusted artist friends mingled with his father\u2019s colleagues. His dad handed him a tray of steaming masala chai to serve. Hesitantly, Rohan used his mother\u2019s lopsided, hand-thrown ceramic cups. Watching a pragmatic engineer cradle the imperfect, beautiful vessel, he felt a click of understanding. It wasn't two separate worlds, but a perfect, harmonious blend. This was the moment he first understood composition, the beauty of the unexpected pairing.\n\n2.\nIt was in Rioja, dust kicking up around his worn boots. He was 22, backpacking and adrift. An old winemaker had him crush a sun-warmed Tempranillo grape between his fingers, then handed him a fistful of the dry, mineral-rich soil. \"This is the parent of that,\" the man said in Spanish. The connection was electric, a current running from the earth, through the vine, to his own palate. It was no longer just wine; it was a story of place. He returned to SF with a clear purpose.\n\n3.\nThe silence of the sommelier certification exam room was deafening. Three red glasses, three whites. His heart hammered, his father\u2019s gentle skepticism a faint echo in his mind. He lifted the first red, inhaled, and the world focused to a single point. Cherry, leather, dried herbs\u2026 Chianti Classico. He named it, his voice steady. The nod from the Master Sommelier was more than confirmation; it was liberation. It was the moment his passion became his irrefutable profession, a craft he had rightfully mastered.\n\n4.\nTheir first night in the Duboce Triangle apartment was chaos. Boxes everywhere. David, ever the architect, was sketching plans on a napkin while Rohan, overwhelmed, opened a bottle he\u2019d been saving\u2014a crisp, celebratory Sancerre. They drank it straight from the bottle, sitting on the bare floor, the city lights painting patterns on the walls. It tasted like potential. In that shared, simple moment, surrounded by unpacked life, Rohan felt truly home. This was the quiet foundation upon which every ambition would be built.\n\n5.\nYesterday\u2019s commute was perfect. The five o\u2019clock sun slanted through the city, making the streetcar lines glitter. He leaned into a turn on his Vespa, the brisk air a sharp, clean palate cleanser after a day of negotiating with distributors. For those 3.5 miles between Duboce and Hayes, he wasn't a director or a boss; he was just a moving part of the city's vibrant ecosystem. It was his daily meditation, a fleeting moment of pure, uncurated freedom that prepared him for the beautiful chaos of service."
